Ad Text:
About GSK

GSK is a global biopharma company with a special purpose – to unite science, technology and talent to get ahead of disease together. Our success depends on our people. We want GSK to be a place where people feel inspired, encouraged and challenged to be their best, where they can grow and thrive.

If you share our ambition, join us at this exciting moment as we get Ahead Together.

 About the role

We are seeking a Customer Insights & Analytics Manager to transform customer‑level data into clear, actionable insights that directly shape our commercial and patient strategies in Australia.

This role is based at our Abbotsford office, with hybrid working arrangements available to support flexibility.

In this senior individual contributor role, you will lead customer targeting, segmentation, territory design, and data‑driven recommendations that improve resource planning and engagement effectiveness. You will work closely with Sales Excellence, Marketing, Market Access, Reporting, and our external data partners to turn complex data into simple, strategic actions.

Your role will be varied and will include:

Leading customer targeting, profiling and segmentation

Designing and optimising territory sizing and alignment

Translating data into insights that support commercial decision making

Ensuring data quality, governance and compliance

 About you

You bring strong analytical capability, commercial acumen and a passion for using data to solve real business problems. You excel in complex environments, can influence without authority, and simplify advanced analytics into clear business language.

You will need:

Bachelor’s degree in statistics, data science, economics, marketing, business or related field

4+ years in customer insights, analytics or market research (healthcare preferred)

Experience with customer targeting, segmentation, territory design or field‑force effectiveness

Strong SQL/Python/R or similar analytical toolkit

 Why join us?

At GSK, we challenge ourselves to get Ahead Together – to make a positive impact on global health, grow our careers, and thrive in a supportive, flexible environment.

By joining GSK, you’ll enjoy:

Flexible, life‑friendly working options

A diverse organisation that reflects the communities we serve

Global development and progression opportunities

5 Feel Good Days + 1 Volunteer Day per year

Option to purchase up to 4 weeks’ additional leave

Access to discounted health insurance

An exciting opportunity has opened up in our Finance team - are you ready to make an impact as our next Business Analyst?

About Us:

Stanbroke is a family-owned and operated Australian cattle and beef business with a proud history of quality, integrity and long-term partnerships. Our operations span across Northern Queensland with extensive cattle properties, backgrounding operations in Southern Queensland, state-of-the-art feedlots, a fully accredited beef processing facility, and global marketing capabilities.
We offer a full range of Grain and Grass-fed beef categories and export to over 40 countries worldwide.

Your Role:

We’re looking for a commercially focused Business Analyst to join our Finance team, reporting directly to the CFO.

This role plays a critical part in delivering accurate reporting, financial modelling, and data-driven insights that support revenue growth and profitability across all Business Units. Working closely with Sales, Operations, and Senior Leadership, you will turn complex data into clear commercial insights that influence key business decisions.

This is a hands-on analytical role suited to someone who enjoys working with numbers, building financial models, and contributing to strategic planning in a fast-paced operational environment.

What You’ll Be Doing:

Report on revenue performance and produce P&L statements for each Business Unit
Prepare Annual Operating Plans, set targets, and forecast revenue
Build and maintain financial and business models to support decision making and maximise profitability
Analyse product costs, production yields, and market data to identify opportunities
Provide actionable insights to support Management, Sales, and Operations
Maintain and develop Power BI reports for daily operations and monthly reporting

What We’re Looking For:

Experience in a Business Analyst, Commercial Analyst or similar analytical finance role
Strong financial modelling and advanced Excel capability
Experience with Power BI or similar reporting and visualisation tools
Ability to interpret large data sets and present clear, actionable insights
Strong communication and stakeholder engagement skills
Commercially minded with a proactive and solutions-focused approach
Tertiary qualifications in Finance, Business, Economics or a related discipline

Why Join Us?

Work closely with senior leadership and influence key commercial decisions
Broad exposure across finance, sales and operational functions
Opportunity to shape reporting and analytics capability within the business
Supportive and collaborative team environment
Careers growth within a large, vertically integrated Australian agribusiness

If you’re a commercially driven analyst who enjoys turning data into meaningful business insights, we’d love to hear from you.

Ad Text:

This role exists to support the critical delivery phase of the FY27 Budget.
It's a hands-on, execution-focused FP&A role, with an immediate priority on budget template ownership, simplification, and governance, followed by deep involvement across budget execution, analytics, and commercial challenge.
You will be accountable for ensuring the FY27 budget cycle is enabled through fit-for-purpose templates, strong analytical oversight, and disciplined coordination across stakeholders.

Own, simplify, and uplift FY27 budget templates ahead of launch

Apply advanced Excel capability including Power Query, VBA, and financial modelling
Embed strong governance, validations, checks, and reconciliation controls

Translate analysis into clear commercial insight and “so what” outcomes

About You
Proven Senior FP&A / Commercial Finance experience
Manufacturing or product-based sector experience (strongly preferred)
Advanced Excel capability is non-negotiable (Power Query, VBA, modelling, governance)

Highly analytical, commercially minded, and delivery-focused
Comfortable handling large data sets and tight timelines
Strong stakeholder engagement skills across Finance and the business
Available to commence immediately or within short notice
What’s in It for You
$140,000 - $150,000 + super
Genuine opportunity to extend or move to permanency
Highly visible role during a critical FY27 budget delivery phase
Hybrid working model (2 days WFH)
Onsite parking & close to public transport
A role where your Excel and FP&A skillset will be genuinely valued and utilised
Please APPLY NOW or contact Declan Stacey for more information on 0483 945 773

Role Title: AI Knowledge Base Engineer
Location: Sydney (preferred) or Melbourne
Start Date: ASAP
Duration: Initial 4‑month contract with high possibility for extension.

NTT Data is seeking a Knowledge Base Engineer to support the build and enhancement of an enterprise-grade, GA‑safe Knowledge Base. This role focuses on ingesting, structuring, tagging, and optimising large volumes of content to enable high‑quality semantic search, retrieval, and grounding. You will work closely with technical and compliance teams to ensure the KB is accurate, structured, compliant, and ready for downstream AI systems.

Is innovation part of your DNA? Do you want to enable a connected future for people, organizations, and society? Join our growing global NTT team and you’ll be part of the world’s largest ICT company (by revenue). We’ve combined the capabilities of 28 remarkable companies to become one, leading technology services provider. Together, we help our people, clients, and communities do great things with technology to create a more secure and connected future. We employ 40,000 people across 57 countries. By bringing together the world’s best technology companies and emerging innovators, we work together to deliver sustainable outcomes to businesses and the world. Innovation is part of our DNA. We believe it’s key to what makes us different. So, we strive to move forward, challenge the status quo, and drive excellence through the technologies we integrate and the services we deliver around the world. The result is connected cities, connected factories, connected healthcare, connected agriculture, connected conservation, connected mobility, and connected sport. Together we enable the connected future.

Key Responsibilities

Build and harden an enterprise-grade, GA‑safe knowledge base
Ingest and structure content from multiple internal and external sources
Implement semantic search pipelines using NLP and vector databases
Define KB schema, metadata models, tagging logic, and filtering rules
Collaborate on the creation of ground‑truth answers and golden datasets
Optimise retrieval quality, coverage, and compliance
Ensure all KB components support safe and auditable AI use

Skills & Experience

Strong background in NLP, semantic search, and vector search technologies
Previous experience with content ingestion, ETL, and data engineering
Exposure to finance, wealth, or superannuation environments advantageous
Hands‑on experience designing structured knowledge bases or information architectures
Ability to identify, classify, and tag risky or compliance‑sensitive content
Strong analytical, documentation, and metadata modelling skills

By monitoring the end-to-end customer journey, you will identify opportunities to optimise marketing spend, improve digital conversion, and enhance service delivery to meet strategic business goals.

The Senior Customer Insights Analyst reports directly to the Chief Customer Officer (CCO) and operates as a key individual contributor. The role serves as a cross-functional hub, collaborating internally with the Senior Leadership Team, Marketing, Digital Product, Sales & Service, IT, Finance, and the Qantas Data and Analytics team.

This permanent full-time position is 100% onsite working from our Byron Bay HeadQuarters or Varsity Lakes Gold Coast office (minimum 1-day per fortnight in HQ), working Monday to Friday, 8-4pm or 9-5pm - you choose!

Strong technical understanding of GA4 and its integration with CRM data.
Desirable experience within the travel or e-commerce sectors, particularly with high-consideration digital purchase journeys.
Desirable experience with a MMM SAAS platform.
Demonstrated ability to translate complex, technical data into simple, actionable insights for non-technical teams.

Seeking a Lead Systems Analyst with a minimum of 5-years systems analyst experience working on cyber security initiatives.
Job details

The Department utilises both cloud and on-prem services, and is uplifting its cyber security posture. A multi-year ICT program has been established to facilitate this objective. A (Systems Analyst) is required to assist with developing detailed mapping documentation to enable cloud migrations. The Systems Analyst will work closely with business units located both domestically and internationally to achieve this objective. The analyst will need to work with internal and external stakeholders (e.g. software vendors) to facilitate automated workflows between dependant systems.

Key duties and responsibilities

The Department requires an ICT infrastructure systems analyst to do the following tasks as part of a multi-skilled team environment:

Examine existing analysis and mapping frameworks to determine if cyber security posture improvements and operational gains are possible,
Liaise, and document learnings, based on discussions with a variety of organisational stakeholders who are located domestically and internationally,
Consolidate and define organisational groups and roles in a format that supports automated migrations,
Develop efficient operating models that work effectively in a distributed, security focused environment,
Facilitate market approaches based on defined criteria,
Collaborate with third-party engineering teams, and internal technical teams, to implement detailed business requirements, and
Assist with transition to service documentation (e.g. standard operating procedures, knowledge base articles).
Essential criteria

A minimum of 5-years systems analyst experience.
High-level interpersonal and written communication skills.
Demonstrated ability to perform analysis and produce deliverables based on existing analysis frameworks.
Proven ability to develop functional and non-functional requirements for large-scale ICT infrastructure projects.
Experience developing documentation to support competitive market approaches.
An understanding of cloud-based services and their interaction with on-prem services. • Ability to produce operating models that work in a distributed, security focused organization. • Collaborate with the third-party engineering teams and internal technical resources to implement business requirements.
Desirable criteria

Experience developing requirements for cloud services.
Experience working on cyber security initiatives.
Contract: 12 Month Contract with 2 x 12 months extension  

Security Required: NV1 Security Clearance required

Location- Canberra based - Hybrid option available - (typically 3 days in the office and 2 days from home) to be negotiated with the successful candidate. Interstate / remote working arrangements will only be considered if a suitable Canberra based candidate cannot be identified. 

How to Apply - Please upload your resume to apply. Candidates will need to be willing to undergo pre-employment screening checks which may include, ID and work rights, security clearance verification and any other client requested checks

Closing date:  Thursday 18 February 2026

Insignia Financial Limited is an Australian financial services company which offers a range of products and services including financial advice, superannuation, investment management and trustee services



Job description:


Own the risk game.
Put your stamp on AI and data governance
Your expertise, your influence, your legacy

The opportunity to join our team

We're looking for a first-line technology risk senior specialist to partner with our Data Automation & AI business unit and to ensure innovation moves swiftly and responsibly. If you thrive on solving complex problems, building trusted relationships, and turning ambiguity into clear, actionable controls, this role is for you.

As we scale data and AI across the enterprise, your mission is to embed practical, business-aligned risk and governance, from data lifecycle and privacy to AI transparency and control testing, so teams can deliver responsibly and confidently. You'll work closely with senior leadership, understand their priorities, and help them navigate incidents, issues, and controls with clarity and confidence.

This is your chance to shape how we build and scale responsible AI and data practices, collaborate with experts in privacy, governance, and control testing, and make a big impact in a fast-moving environment. You'll join an enthusiastic, supportive team with a strong culture, enjoy autonomy to shape the role and make it your own, and work across the entire enterprise for huge exposure and influence. Plus, you'll have the opportunity to mentor, influence frameworks, and leave your mark.

Key Responsibilities:

Advise on data risk and technology governance controls aligned to frameworks and regulations (APRA CPS 230/234, CPG 235)
Implement risk uplift programs and embed data governance practices across Technology
Assess and monitor risks for data-driven and AI-enabled initiatives; manage incidents and issues
Establish and advise on AI governance frameworks, transparency, and emerging regulations
Develop key risk indicators and metrics for AI and data risks
Mentor junior team members and collaborate with privacy, technology governance, and control testing teams

What you will bring

Proven risk/compliance experience in 1st line technology risk (financial services preferred)
Strong knowledge of APRA requirements and data governance frameworks
Experience with data lifecycle management, retention, and quality controls
Ability to analyse complex data/AI risk scenarios and provide actionable recommendations
Exceptional stakeholder engagement and communication skills, including board-level reporting
Interest in AI, automation, and bots; ability to work autonomously and in a team

Find the better way

What gets us excited about working here? Helping people feel good about their money as one of Australia's leading financial wellbeing organisations. From those starting out to those retiring. As your team, we'll show up for you and together we will create financial wellbeing for every Australian. Because we know people who are confident about their financial future live better lives.

If this sounds like your kind of career, you sound like our kind of person. With us, you'll do work that builds your technical know-how and challenges our entire industry to move forward. Along the way, you'll be free to explore new ideas and technology, solve problems in a team, and independently to get great things done. Around here, we like to call it "putting our fingerprints on the future".

People-inspired tech

Deep expertise combined with creativity can take on the trickiest of problems. Join our team of brilliant minds and mentors as we explore our way to innovation and apply technology in more human ways than ever.

To Apply

Senior Security Data Pipeline & SIEM Engineer (NV1 Required)

Location: Canberra
Engagement: Contract
Clearance: Active NV1 Security Clearance

A major program of work is underway to uplift security telemetry, log rationalisation, and SOC onboarding capabilities across a large, complex environment. We’re seeking an experienced Security Data Pipeline, SIEM & Data Engineering Specialist to join the team and help deliver scalable, modern, and cost?efficient security data architectures.

This role is ideal for a senior engineer who thrives in high?volume data environments, understands modern security logging ecosystems, and can design and optimise pipelines that support next?generation SOC operations.

What You’ll Be Doing


Designing and implementing advanced security data pipelines (Cribl, Splunk DMX, Kafka?based).
Architecting and optimising Security Data Lakes (AWS Security Lake, Snowflake, Delta Lake, Microsoft Fabric).
Configuring and managing SIEM platforms such as Splunk ES or Microsoft Sentinel.
Developing log rationalisation, enrichment, suppression, and parsing strategies.
Building scalable ingestion frameworks, schema management, and ETL/ELT processes.
Enabling federated search and cross?platform analytics across SIEM and data lake environments.
Supporting SOC onboarding, including SOAR, threat intel, and case management integrations.
Conducting performance benchmarking, readiness assessments, and architecture validation.
Producing documentation, runbooks, and knowledge?transfer materials.
What You Bring


Active NV1 Security Clearance (essential).
5+ years in security engineering, SIEM engineering, or security data platforms.
Strong data engineering experience across log ingestion, transformation, and distributed systems.
Hands?on expertise with at least one major pipeline technology (Cribl Stream, Splunk DMX, Fluentd, Logstash).
Experience with modern data lakes (AWS Security Lake, Snowflake, Delta Lake, Microsoft Fabric).
Proficiency with SIEM platforms such as Splunk ES or Microsoft Sentinel.
Strong scripting/automation skills (Python, SQL, PowerShell).
Familiarity with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP).
Experience with SOC onboarding workflows, SOAR, ticketing, and threat intelligence integrations.
Excellent communication and documentation skills.

Your new team

Working as part of the Technology GRISC and Security Team the Senior Technology Governance, Risk Information Security and Compliance Analyst will have input into the technical direction of the Technology GRISC Team and influence and support key business stakeholders. The role will include the responsibilities for supporting the Technology Division in meeting regulatory and compliance obligations as well as general organisational information security and risk practices.
A large portion of the goals includes a transformation of the culture and the approach to risk in operations and decision making.

The role

Leadership

Influence and support the ongoing development of the security roadmap.
Be an ambassador for security working across the business to provide effective communication on security matters and build relationships with other teams to ensure effective dialogue between departments.
Continually support and strengthen the Auto & General brand and culture by personally modelling high standards of performance, positively influencing teams and individuals, negotiating and resolving conflict, and articulating and cascading the Company vision and objective

Job Specific

Enhancing and maintaining the Security Controls Testing Framework and the Information Security Management System.
Enhancing and maintaining vendor due-diligence processes, lead and define overall third party risk management efforts.
Creating reports for management regarding Governance Risk, and Compliance related topics.
Tracking and reporting on key risk indicators(KRIs)
Define and influence the appropriate security controls are applied throughout the system/continual monitoring lifecycle.
Perform security and compliance assessments on new and existing systems, processes, and technology.
Work with various business units to ensure controls are adequate, appropriate, and effective.
Support internal and external audit processes.
Weigh the relevancy, accuracy and perspective of conclusions against internal and external audit evidence.
Perform business impact analysis and assist with the development of the Technology risk register.
Interface with Technology and business in general to provide guidance and support.
Stay up to date and informed on developing regulatory concerns and changing IT and information security trends.

Risk and Compliance

This role contributes to A&G’S commitment to adhering to the regulatory framework overseen by APRA. You will be involved in:

Learning and understanding APRA's prudential standards and guidelines, supporting their implementation within the organisation
Assisting with the identification and assessment of operational, financial, and reputational risks associated with the organisation's activities.
Contributing to the development and maintenance of a robust risk management framework, including policies, procedures, and controls.
